title: $:/plugins/linonetwo/autocomplete/changelog

! Changelog

!! Version 0.9.6

* Fixed: Aligned `filterTiddlersAsync` IPC option name with TidGi Desktop PR #719 — renamed `ignoreSyncSystemConfig` to `skipSystemFilter`. This fixes multi-run filter corruption where combining multiple filter runs (e.g. `+[search:title[foo]] +[search:alias[foo]] +[search:caption[foo]]`) only returned results from the last run.
* Fixed: `search-sidebar-tab` now fetches sidebar tabs via IPC (`filterTiddlersAsync`) instead of DOM scraping, consistent with other system-mode sources.
* Changed: `buildTitleFieldFilter` now searches all title-like fields (title, alias, caption) in a single filter run, preventing duplicate results when the IPC backend returns union results from a combined multi-field search.

!! Version 0.9.5

* Fixed: TitleAlias with multiple fields (e.g. `title caption alias`) now searches fields as a union instead of an intersection, so matching a tiddler by its title no longer fails just because its caption doesn't match.
* Fixed: corrected swapped `sourceId` values between `search-recent` (`recent-searches`) and `search-story-history` (`story-history`) that broke Ctrl+Tab cycle-history navigation.
* Fixed: Ctrl+Tab cycle-history mode now shows the full story history even when the query is empty.
* Fixed: search queries containing `]` are now sanitized before being inserted into TiddlyWiki filter strings, preventing `Missing [ in filter expression` errors.
* Fixed: empty TextAlias config no longer triggers an unintended all-fields search.
* Fixed: `action-variable-prompt` string coalescing and added a bounds check for prompt definitions.
* Fixed: various ESLint errors and TypeScript type issues in source plugins and utilities.
* Changed: default TitleAlias config now includes the `alias` field (`title caption alias`).
* Changed: default TextAlias config now includes the `keywords` field (`text keywords`).
* Changed: aligned project dependencies, scripts, `tsconfig.json`, `dprint.json`, `playwright.config.ts`, and Husky/CI workflows with the Modern.TiddlyDev template.
* Added: comprehensive Jasmine unit tests for title, text, system-title, ignore-filter, story-history, filter ordering, and source-id correctness.
* Added: Playwright E2E regressions for searching by title, caption, and alias fields.

!! Version 0.9.4

* Fixed: entering `$` (dollar sign), `¥` (half-width yen), or `￥` (full-width yen) in system mode now correctly shows the layout list by default. The system prefix config now includes all three symbols.
* Changed: removed deprecated `emptyContext` export, `checkIsModalPromptActive`, and `checkIsUnderFilter` helpers from internal utils. Callers now use `contextReducer(contextActions.clearTransient())` directly.
* Changed: removed deprecated `IBrowserViewMetaData.workspaceID` field; use `workspace` instead.
* Added: Playwright regressions for `$`, `¥`, and `￥` layout list display, including a case that verifies the default layout appears with no extra layouts installed.

!! Version 0.9.3

* Fixed: each autocomplete sub-plugin now uses an independent debounce instance, preventing multiple sources from cancelling each other's search results.
* Fixed: IME composition placeholder spaces no longer trigger full-text searches, reducing panel open lag.
* Fixed: `story-list` source returns an empty array on empty queries and limits results to 20 items, preventing large history lists from causing UI freezes.

!! Version 0.9.2

* Added: sidebar tab search in system mode, with switching support and matching on both tab title and rendered caption.
* Added: Playwright regressions for sidebar-tab search and switching.
* Fixed: system queries like `open` and `tool` no longer falsely match the default layout through the layout source.

!! Version 0.9.1

* Fixed: title search ignore filters now only suppress title-like fields by default; caption matches remain searchable.
* Changed: removed pinyin search support and related pinyin dependency from autocomplete.

!! Version 0.9.0

* Added: centralized source routing via `phaseRouter.ts` to make autocomplete mode switching consistent.
* Fixed: action-variable prompt now stays isolated from other sources and closes the panel correctly after wizard selection.
* Added: Playwright regressions for command palette wizard flows.

!! Version 0.8.0

* Added: `text` action-variable autocomplete via `<variable>/autocomplete-filter`.
* Added: `select` action-variable type with dynamic options from `<variable>/autocomplete-filter`.
* Added: `multi-checkbox` action-variable type. Selected options are written as list variables.
* Added: support for `<variable>/options` static option list, merged with dynamic options.

!! Version 0.7.0

* Added: declarative action variable wizard for action-string commands.
** Use `action-variables` as a list field to declare variables.
** Define each variable with `<variable>/type`, `<variable>/caption`, `<variable>/description`, `<variable>/default`.
** Supported input types: `text`, `checkbox` (writes `yes` or `no` into action variables).
* Changed: command-action-string no longer contains hardcoded `open-create-tiddler-wizard` branch.
* Fixed: improved translation rendering cache key with language and variable context.
* Fixed: compatibility with TiddlyWiki 5.4.0-prerelease by using quoted lingo override base argument.


!! Version 0.6.2

* Fixed: action-string and message command items no longer open their tiddlers when activated; Enter and click now only execute the command and behave identically.

!! Version 0.6.0

* ''Breaking Change'': Requires TidGi-Desktop version 0.13.0 or higher
** Updated API usage: replaced `window?.meta?.()?.workspaceID` with `window?.meta?.()?.workspace`
